                <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/disqus/">
                    Disqus
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">2 days ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>How many Americans bother to place a credit freeze on their credit reports? A freeze makes it much more difficult for a merchant or other grantor of credit to access your credit report and so is far less likely to grant credit to the identity thief. A credit freeze is much less expensive than a credit monitoring service and probably more effective.</p> 
<p>While the phone sellers will end up eating any losses, the identity theft victims will have to spend many hours untangling their damaged credit.</p>

    	</div>



